    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>parsley</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and <strong>chopped onion</strong> to a baking tray (or two!) with 1/2 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 10-15 min or until the onion is cooked and starting to crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tomato and onion is cooking, add your<strong> bulgur wheat </strong>with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot and set aside until later</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>halloumi</strong> into 3 pieces per person</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine the juice of your<strong> lime[s] </strong>with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>, your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>oregano </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>in a medium bowl</p><p>Give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>herb marinade</strong></p><p>Dip the <strong>halloumi</strong> in the <strong>herb marinade </strong>(reserve any remaining marinade)</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> coated halloumi </strong>to the pan and cook for 1-2 min on each side until almost browning, add the<strong> remaining herb marinade</strong> to the pan and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Once done, transfer to a chopping board and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>zingy halloumi</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roughly chop your<strong> cucumber</strong> and add to a bowl with your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!)</p><p>Season with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tzatziki</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> roasted vegetables</strong> and <strong>chopped parsley</strong> to the pot with the cooked bulgur<strong> </strong>and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Mediterranean-style</strong> <strong>veg bulgur</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/zingy-halloumi-and-veg-bulgur/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> zingy halloumi </strong>over the <strong>Mediterranean-style veg</strong> <strong>bulgur</strong> with the<strong> tzatziki</strong> on the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
